[[File:Dörte-Mueritz2013.jpg|thumb|upright|Haftendorn in 2013]]
'''Dörte Haftendorn''' (born March 25, 1948){{r|born}} is a German mathematician, [[mathematics education|mathematics educator]], and textbook author who works as a professor at [[Leuphana University of Lüneburg]].{{r|cv}}

Haftendorn earned her Ph.D. in 1975 from the [[Clausthal University of Technology]]. Her dissertation, ''Additiv kommutative und idempotente Halbringe mit Faktorbedingung'', was supervised by Hanns J. Weinert.{{r|mgp}} She taught at the Johanneum gymnasium in Lüneburg from 1975 until 2002, when she became a professor at Leuphana University of Lüneburg.{{r|cv}}

She is the author of two German-language mathematics textbooks, ''Mathematik sehen und verstehen'' [Seeing and understanding mathematics] (Spektrum, 2010; 2nd ed., 2015){{r|msv}} and ''Kurven erkunden und verstehen'' [Exploring and understanding curves] (Spektrum, 2016).{{r|kev}}

